ly-than-digital-because-supply-noise-directly-contaminates-signal-measurements","line":34},{"title":"78xx-regulators-require-input-and-output-capacitors-close-to-pins-for-stability","target":"78xx-regulators-require-input-and-output-capacitors-close-to-pins-for-stability","line":35},{"title":"passives","target":"passives","line":38},{"title":"eda-fundamentals","target":"eda-fundamentals","line":39}],"metadata":{"description":"Digital IC switching draws sharp current spikes from the supply rail -- a 100nF ceramic capacitor placed as close as possible to VCC/GND pins acts as a local charge reservoir that absorbs these transients before they propagate and cause voltage dips","type":"knowledge-note","source":"docs/parts/100nf-ceramic-capacitor-104-50v-decoupling-bypass.md","topics":["[[passives]]","[[eda-fundamentals]]"],"confidence":"proven","verified":true},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[],"key":"knowledge/every-digital-ic-requires-a-100nf-ceramic-decoupling-capacitor-between-vcc-and-gnd-to-absorb-switching-transients.md"},"smart_blocks:knowledge/every-digital-ic-requires-a-100nf-ceramic-decoupling-capacitor-between-vcc-and-gnd-to-absorb-switching-transients.md#---frontmatter---": {"path":null,"last_embed":{"hash":"14fsedm","at":1776207197485},"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.06328923,0.05215942,0.08031274,-0.01836102,-0.03470729,0.00338708,0.03665631,0.04663615,-0.01961451,-0.03123099,0.00730712,-0.08440332,0.0234583,0.0377406,0.0511403,0.0576082,-0.06534991,-0.02979352,0.05121459,0.05133475,0.08462764,-0.02615664,-0.00975541,-0.03231102,0.05228154,-0.01765855,0.09177888,-0.0282728,-0.0628614,-0.25344974,-0.03289219,0.02514096,-0.00371065,-0.04520128,-0.01830529,-0.0580975,-0.02854603,-0.01058753,-0.00404578,0.01162644,0.00620509,-0.0028826,-0.02921971,-0.062755,0.02065677,-0.02716774,-0.06242535,-0.0367622,0.05795936,-0.0021993,0.02188094,0.02133677,0.04738034,-0.02009902,-0.01651433,0.06970637,0.03002637,0.04342438,0.10829243,0.01499